      {
        "id": "ec6a0bbe41bb0a7d56155aa467c74ec636ae9817",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-10 15:41:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks for the feedback Ram - in an oom installation, see this file, line 18:  https://git.onap.org/oom/tree/kubernetes/policy/charts/mariadb/resources/config/db.sh\n\nThose are all the DBs in use by existing policy components.\n\nIn general, not sure if using all the same database is the way to go for all components.   I can see synergy though for api and pap though.   But it wouldn't make much sense in my opinion that for example pap would see runtime db data only specific to the drools component just to say.   Further, as the components evolve in their own cycles, let's say I want to bring it a new image version of drools into the lab, messing up some DB operations, will affect all the other components.  I think is better to keep them isolated into functionality groups.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
